wrapScienceJ.wrapImaJ.core

Interface ImageCalibration

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    ImageCalibrationGeneric, ImageCalibrationIJ

    public interface ImageCalibration
    Allows to manage non isotropic images, and to store and access voxel's sizes and volume

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      void debugAttributes()
      Writes the attributes (calibration data) on the standard error stream.
      java.lang.String getUnitLength()
      Allows to retrieve the unit length within an image e.g. in micro-meters ("µm" or "microns") for microscopy images, in centimeters for MNR images, etc.
      double getVolume()
      Retrieves the volume of each Voxel in a given unit e.g. in cubic micro-meters for microscopy images, in cubic centimeters for MNR images, etc.
      double getVoxelDepth()
      Retrieves the depth of a voxel according to the (possibly non isotropic) image's calibration data.

      • getVoxelLength

        VoxelDouble getVoxelLength()
        Retrieves the edges lengths of each Voxel in a given unit e.g. in micro-meters for microscopy images, in centimeters for MNR images, etc.
        Returns:
        A voxel the coordinates of which give edges lengths for the voxels of an image

      • getVolume

        double getVolume()
        Retrieves the volume of each Voxel in a given unit e.g. in cubic micro-meters for microscopy images, in cubic centimeters for MNR images, etc.
        Returns:
